        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Code verification acceptance criteria — COU2",
        "description": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to the Navier-Stokes solver and the hemolysis power-law transport equation; observed order of convergence must be within 10% of theoretical order."
      },
      "rationale": "MMS verification performed on both the flow solver and hemolysis scalar transport equation. Observed spatial order of convergence is 1.92 (theoretical 2.0), within the 10% tolerance. Temporal order is 1.87 (theoretical 2.0). Wide uncertainty bands on hemolysis scalar transport (±18% at 95% CI) are explicitly documented in the Monte Carlo UQ report; they reflect genuine model-form uncertainty rather than code errors. Achieved level 3 equals required level 3."
