        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — COU2",
        "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) computed on three systematically refined meshes; GCI on hemolysis index QoI must be <5% at the operating point of maximum hemolysis."
      },
      "rationale": "Three-mesh Richardson extrapolation performed. GCI on hemolysis index is 4.1% at the maximum-hemolysis operating point (Q=4 L/min, 3500 RPM), satisfying the <5% criterion. Confidence in GCI estimate is approximately 50% due to non-monotonic convergence observed at Q=6 L/min; this is honestly documented in the mesh convergence validation result and UQ report. Despite the wide bound, the criterion is met at the critical operating point."
    },
    {
