        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance acceptance criteria — COU2",
        "description": "The CFD QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint (plasma-free hemoglobin concentration) via a documented physiological mapping with cited literature support."
      },
      "rationale": "NIH is mapped to plasma-free hemoglobin via the ASTM F1841 standard protocol. Literature review (5 peer-reviewed sources cited in the evidence package) confirms the mapping is accepted in the field. Confidence is approximately 50% because the power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) has known limitations at low-shear regions; this limitation is explicitly stated in the rationale and reflected in the wide Monte Carlo bounds. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
