        "name": "Validation relevance acceptance criteria — COU2",
        "description": "Validation experiments must use the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry (not a surrogate geometry) and must span the intended operating envelope of the VAD COU (flow rates 2–6 L/min, speeds 2500–4000 RPM)."
      },
      "rationale": "All validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry with confirmed dimensional tolerances (±0.05 mm). Operating conditions span Q=2, 3, 4, 5, 6 L/min at 2500, 3000, 3500, 4000 RPM — fully covering the COU envelope. Confidence is approximately 50% because only one laboratory conducted the experiments, limiting inter-laboratory reproducibility assessment; this is explicitly flagged as a limitation in the validation result record. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
